QueryText: NURSERY PREPARATION  FOR ONION ?
KCCAns: This is the most common method practiced for irrigated crop as it results in high yield and large size bulbs. In plains, seeds are sown during October-November for a rabi crop.  Seeds are first sown in well prepared nursery beds of 90-120 cm width, 7.5-10.0 cm height and convenient length. Ratio between nursery area and main field is about 1:20. Seed rate varies from 8 to 10 kg/ha. Seedlings of 15 cm height and 0.8 cm neck diameter are ideal for transplanting and this is achieved in 8 weeks. However, it varies from 6-10 weeks depending on soil, climate and receipt of rain. There is a practice of topping seedlings at the time of transplanting if seedlings are over-grown.

QueryText: HOW TO CONTROL Bacterial Wilt in potato ?
KCCAns:
•Splitting of the tubers at the time of the planting should be avoided as splitting spreads the disease even to health tubers.
•Application of stable bleaching powder (12kg/ha) mixed with fertilizer in furrows while planting reduces wilt incidence by 80%.
•Practicing crop rotation for 2-3 years with crops like maize, finger millet, cereals, garlic,  and onion cabbage can reduce the disease inoculum.

QueryText: HOW TO CONTROL Bacterial Wilt in potato ?
KCCAns:

•Application of stable bleaching powder (12kg/ha) mixed with fertilizer in furrows while planting reduces wilt incidence by 80%.
